Their apprehensions stem from several anticipated changes in celestial bodies, specifically: 
* that the Earth, due to the Sun's gradual approach towards it, will eventually be absorbed or engulfed over time; 
* that the Sun's surface will progressively become encrusted with its own emissions, ultimately ceasing to illuminate the world; 
* that the Earth narrowly avoided a catastrophic encounter with the tail of the most recent comet, which would have inevitably reduced it to ashes; 
* and that the next predicted comet, calculated to arrive thirty-one years from now, will likely bring about our destruction.
